</p></entry><entry colname="col3" namest="col3" nameend="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the voltages from the EC internal power supply 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the PSU output: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">1) Short out pins 15 and 16 on the 24-pin motherboard power connector with a small piece of wire. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7626B55A-522E-4177-A8BA-A9D5CD196337" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-92A5EC95-6B3B-4E7A-AC27-00BEA0150528-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-92A5EC95-6B3B-4E7A-AC27-00BEA0150528-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect the negative probe on the multimeter (black) to any ground wired pin and connect the positive probe (red) to the first power line you want to test. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The 24-pin main power connector has +3.3 VDC, +5 VDC, -5 VDC (optional), +12 VDC, and -12 VDC lines across multiple pins. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the short 
